`libmavsdk-dev` is **not available in the Ubuntu 24.04 APT repositories**. The official MAVSDK project now recommends downloading the prebuilt `.deb` package from its GitHub releases instead of using `apt`. ([MAVSDK][1])

### Step 1: Check your Ubuntu version

```bash
lsb_release -a
```

You should see:

```
Ubuntu 24.04.x LTS
```

### Step 2: Download the Ubuntu 24.04 package

```bash
wget https://github.com/mavlink/MAVSDK/releases/download/v3.0.0/libmavsdk-dev_3.0.0_ubuntu24.04_amd64.deb
```

### Step 3: Install it

```bash
sudo dpkg -i libmavsdk-dev_3.0.0_ubuntu24.04_amd64.deb
```

If there are missing dependencies:

```bash
sudo apt --fix-broken install
```

Then run:

```bash
sudo dpkg -i libmavsdk-dev_3.0.0_ubuntu24.04_amd64.deb
```

### Step 4: Verify

```bash
pkg-config --modversion mavsdk
```

or

```bash
dpkg -l | grep mavsdk
```

